\begin{align*}
a^2 - b^2 &= -77, \\
2ab &= -36.
\end{align*}Dividing the second equation by the first, we get $\frac{2ab}{a^2 - b^2} = \frac{-36}{-77} = \frac{36}{77},$ so $\frac{2}{\frac{a}{b}} = \frac{36}{77},$ but $\frac{a}{b} = \tan(\arg(z)),$ so $\cot(\arg(z)) = \frac{77}{18},$ and $\tan^2(\arg(z)) + \cot^2(\arg(z)) = \sec^2(\arg(z)) = 1 + \frac{77^2}{18^2} = \frac{7025}{324}.$ By the AM-HM inequality, we have \[\frac{77 + 18}{2} \ge \sqrt{\frac{77^2 + 18^2}{2}},\]with equality if and only if $77 = 18,$ which is not the case, so the maximum value of $\tan^2(\arg(z)) + \cot^2(\arg(z))$ is $\frac{9}{2},$ which gives $ tim(\arg(z)) = \pm \frac{\sqrt{81}}{18} = \pm \frac{9}{18} = \pm \frac{1}{2}.$ Equating imaginary parts, we get $2ab = -36,$ so $ab = -18$ and $a = \pm \frac{18}{b},$ and $b = \pm \sqrt{36(9 - b^2)}.$

